      'Where am I in the Fourth-Sun-flood narrative — what *era of my life is ending in water* (the relationship-being-flooded-by-tears, the project-being-washed-out, the life-chapter-being-cosmically-cleansed), and have I begun *the becoming-fish* (the species-changing-transformation that surviving the cosmic-cleansing-flood requires)?',
      'Whose Chalchiuhtlicue have I refused to recognize — what *cosmic-feminine-of-surface-water* in my life (a mother, a grandmother, a midwife-figure, the body-of-water-near-my-home) has been *quietly bathing-everything-newly-arrived* without acknowledgment, and what would *honoring-the-bathing-without-which-no-cleansing-happens* look like?'
